The paper discusses a new decision theory that aims to maximize utility in various decision problems, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses mathematical functions to determine the best outcome, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the paper explores philosophical justifications for the new theory, which could be relevant to social and information sciences (cs.SI).
